description:
We are looking for a Data Analyst for an international project of a European Union agency (EU).

Ideal candidates should have:
• Formal training in ArcGIS;
• Training in enterprise GIS technologies such as ESRI ArcGIS Server/SDE;
• Training in ArcGIS for SharePoint and ArcGIS API for Silverlight and JavaScript;
• During the past five years:
• At least three years of experience in geodata management and analysis;
• At least three years of experience in using ArcGIS Desktop Suite;
• At least five years of experience in geodata processing and cartography;

Responsabilities
• Support and manage GIS applications, including GIS web services;
• Oversee data flow, management and distribution activities to support GIS;
• Build and maintain GIS databases;
• Create static and dynamic maps using ArcGIS;
• Maintain geospatial documentations for reference purposes;
• Work in compliance with GIS standards and quality policies;
• Provide technical guidance to GIS users when needed;
• Assist technical... team in system design and development;

Company

Being part of THEWHITEAM is to collaborate with a company formed by professionals with extensive experience in technology consulting.

We firmly believe that companies and clients mark the way forward in the sector, but this is built by people. We consider it vitally important that our organisation is based on our best asset and value-added brand, which is our team.

Benefits

On the other hand, I also leave you a small summary of the company's policies so that you can get to know us a little better:
• Our agreement is that of Consultancy and market research companies.
• We have 23 days holiday a year
• The company gives us the day of our birthday as a gift, so that we can enjoy it without working.
• We have 14 payments, 12 monthly and two extra ones (June and December).
• As flexible remuneration we can ask for a childcare voucher and also medical + dental insurance

